gov.nih.nlm.meme.action
Class Version

java.lang.Object
  gov.nih.nlm.meme.action.Version
public class Version
extends Object

The Version class provides package version information for gov.nih.nlm.meme.action package. History

01/25/2005:
Minor changes to molecular actions. Certain ones should not even bother to compute CUIs (like relationship/attribute actions). Also, we now have slightly improved toString() methods for "move" and "split" actions that list the atom ids involved. LoggedAction.removeSubAction(LoggedAction). New Recipe and RecipeStep classes.
01/14/2005:
MEMEDataSourceAction and MIDDataSourceAction interfaces have better javadoc comments. LoggedAction now defines getInverseAction The various MEMEDataSourceAction and MIDDataSourceAction implementations now use getInitialState and getInverseAction. We have a new NonOperationAction for handling the inverse action of things that do not have an invers. NextIdentifierAction was changed slightly so serializing it did not require writing a field of type Class to the file. This caused that weird array store exception. It now stores the class name as a string. MolecularApproveConceptAction had a bug fix relating to the function that converts C level RT? or LK rels to RT when the concept is approved. IT now does this properly. MolecularMergeAction was allowing a situation where a C level rel would remain status N while a demotion overlapped it. This hole in the logic was repaired. If the problem persists, it is likely from move/split actions. AtomicAction implementations no longer have constructors for ConceptMapping objects.
12/13/2004:
MolecularAction has a switch to control whether it causes a CUI assignemtn MEMEDataSourceActions now have a getInitialState() method. MIDDataSourceActions now have a getInitialState() method. New actions: SystemStatusAction, CuiAction, MatrixAction, ExecAction, QueryAction, LoadTableAction
11/05/2004:
This is the first version of the action package. All actions from the client package were moved here and the client ones were made to extend these (and were then deprecated). This package was created as part of an ambitious project to overhaul action handling and logging in MEME4 with the eventual goal of having every change to the database be represented as a MEME4 action which can be logged and synchronized with MRD.

Author:
MEME Group
